  "text": "## gRPC Error Status Propagation Across Three Major Go Services\n\nThis analysis compares how gRPC error status codes are created and propagated to HTTP responses across kubernetes/kubernetes, etcd-io/etcd, and grafana/grafana.\n\n### Kubernetes (kubernetes/kubernetes)\n\n**Error Creation Pattern:**\nKubernetes creates gRPC errors at service boundaries. Key examples:\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/kubelet/pkg/cri/streaming/errors.go:NewErrorTooManyInFlight()` creates `status.Error(codes.ResourceExhausted, ...)`\n- `test/e2e/storage/drivers/csi-test/mock/service/node.go` uses `status.Error(codes.NotFound, ...)` and `status.Error(codes.Internal, ...)`\n- Generated service code in `staging/src/k8s.io/kms/apis/v2/api_grpc.pb.go` returns `status.Errorf(codes.Unimplemented, ...)`\n\n**HTTP Translation Pattern:**\nThe translation from gRPC to HTTP uses a switch statement mapping gRPC codes to HTTP status codes:\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/kubelet/pkg/cri/streaming/errors.go:WriteError()` - Core translation function:\n  - `codes.NotFound` → `http.StatusNotFound`\n  - `codes.ResourceExhausted` → `http.StatusTooManyRequests`\n  - Default → `http.StatusInternalServerError`\n\n- `vendor/github.com/grpc-ecosystem/grpc-gateway/v2/runtime/errors.go:HTTPStatusFromCode()` - Comprehensive mapping:\n  - `codes.OK` → `200`\n  - `codes.InvalidArgument` → `400`\n  - `codes.DeadlineExceeded` → `504`\n  - `codes.NotFound` → `404`\n  - `codes.PermissionDenied` → `403`\n  - `codes.Unauthenticated` → `401`\n\n**Error Propagation Chain:**\n- Service implementations return gRPC status errors\n- `pkg/volume/util/metrics.go:getErrorCode()` extracts status codes for metrics\n- `pkg/probe/grpc/grpc.go:Probe()` handles codes like `codes.Unimplemented` and `codes.DeadlineExceeded`\n- HTTP handlers use `WriteError()` to translate before responding\n\n### etcd-io/etcd\n\n**Error Creation Pattern:**\netcd uses pre-defined gRPC error variables with specific codes, centralized in `api/v3rpc/rpctypes/error.go`:\n- Server-side errors defined with status codes:\n  - `ErrGRPCEmptyKey = status.Error(codes.InvalidArgument, ...)`\n  - `ErrGRPCLeaseNotFound = status.Error(codes.NotFound, ...)`\n  - `ErrGRPCMemberExist = status.Error(codes.FailedPrecondition, ...)`\n  - `ErrGRPCNoLeader = status.Error(codes.Unavailable, ...)`\n  - `ErrGRPCInvalidAuthToken = status.Error(codes.Unauthenticated, ...)`\n  - `ErrGRPCPermissionDenied = status.Error(codes.PermissionDenied, ...)`\n  - `ErrGRPCCorrupt = status.Error(codes.DataLoss, ...)`\n\n**HTTP Translation Pattern:**\netcd uses `toGRPCErrorMap` to translate internal errors to gRPC errors in `server/etcdserver/api/v3rpc/util.go:togRPCError()`:\n- Maps domain errors (e.g., `membership.ErrIDNotFound`) to gRPC status errors\n- Falls back to `status.Error(codes.Unknown, ...)` for unmapped errors\n- Handles context errors specially: `context.Canceled` and `context.DeadlineExceeded` are passed through\n\nHTTP responses are handled in `server/etcdserver/api/etcdhttp/peer.go`:\n- `membership.ErrIDNotFound` → `http.StatusNotFound`\n- `membership.ErrMemberNotLearner` → `http.StatusPreconditionFailed`\n- `errors.ErrLearnerNotReady` → `http.StatusPreconditionFailed`\n\n**Error Propagation Chain:**\n1. Business logic in etcdserver generates domain errors\n2. `server/etcdserver/api/v3rpc/util.go:togRPCError()` converts to gRPC status errors\n3. `server/etcdserver/api/v3rpc/interceptor.go` - unary and stream interceptors enforce capabilities and return errors\n4. `client/v3/retry_interceptor.go:contextErrToGRPCErr()` - client-side handler converts context errors to gRPC status\n5. HTTP handlers in `peer.go` translate to HTTP status codes\n\n### Grafana (grafana/grafana)\n\n**Error Creation Pattern:**\nGrafana creates gRPC errors at service boundaries:\n- `pkg/services/authz/rbac/service.go:ListPermission()` - `status.Error(codes.NotFound, \"unsupported resource\")`\n- Service implementation returns gRPC status errors directly\n\n**HTTP Translation Pattern:**\nGrafana uses grpc-gateway middleware to convert gRPC errors:\n- `pkg/services/authz/zanzana/server/openfga_server.go:NewOpenFGAHttpServer()` uses:\n  - `runtime.WithErrorHandler()` - Custom HTTP error handler\n  - `runtime.WithStreamErrorHandler()` - Stream error handler\n  - Calls `serverErrors.ConvertToEncodedErrorCode(status.Convert(e))` to convert gRPC status\n  - Calls `httpmiddleware.CustomHTTPErrorHandler()` to write HTTP response\n\n- `pkg/storage/unified/resource/errors.go:HTTPStatusFromCode()` - Maps gRPC codes to HTTP:\n  - Uses `runtime.HTTPStatusFromCode(st.Code())` for standard mapping\n  - Falls back to `500` for unmapped codes\n\n**Error Propagation Chain:**\n1. Service methods return gRPC status errors\n2. `pkg/tsdb/influxdb/fsql/fsql.go:Query()` - Receives gRPC errors from FlightSQL client\n3. Checks `status.FromError(err)` and switches on `grpcStatusErr.Code()`:\n   - `codes.InvalidArgument` → `backend.StatusBadRequest`\n   - `codes.PermissionDenied` → `backend.StatusForbidden`\n   - `codes.NotFound` → `backend.StatusNotFound`\n   - `codes.Unavailable` → `http.StatusServiceUnavailable`\n   - `codes.Unauthenticated` → `backend.StatusUnauthorized`\n   - Default → `backend.StatusInternal`\n4. grpc-gateway middleware translates to HTTP before returning to client\n5. `pkg/plugins/manager/client/client.go` - Handles `codes.Canceled` for request cancellation\n6. `pkg/plugins/backendplugin/grpcplugin/client_v2.go:handleGrpcStatusError()` - Error source handling\n\n### Key Patterns and Differences\n\n**Centralized vs Distributed Error Creation:**\n- **etcd**: Centralized in `rpctypes/error.go` - all gRPC errors defined once\n- **Kubernetes**: Distributed at call sites - errors created where needed\n- **Grafana**: Mix - some pre-defined, some created at call sites\n\n**Error Mapping Strategies:**\n- **etcd**: Explicit `toGRPCErrorMap` for domain-to-gRPC conversion\n- **Kubernetes**: Use grpc-gateway's built-in HTTP status mapping\n- **Grafana**: Custom middleware with `status.Convert()` and error handler callbacks\n\n**Propagation Mechanisms:**\n- **etcd**: Context errors flow through interceptors unchanged; handled separately\n- **Kubernetes**: Direct mapping at HTTP boundaries via `WriteError()`\n- **Grafana**: grpc-gateway middleware abstracts the translation\n\n**Code Organization:**\n- **etcd**: Clear separation in `rpctypes/error.go` (creation) and `v3rpc/util.go` (translation)\n- **Kubernetes**: Vendored grpc-gateway handles translation; service code creates errors\n- **Grafana**: Service code creates errors; gateway middleware handles translation"
